---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title='Plasterers & Painters in Pinner | Hancock' description='Plastering and painting in Pinner. Fixed-price quotes from City & Guilds certified contractors covering Pinner and the surrounding area.' activePage='areas'>
<section style="position:relative;height:340px;display:flex;align-items:flex-end;">
  <div style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;right:0;bottom:0;background-image:url('/uploads/Hancock-plastering-and-painting%20(5).webp');background-size:cover;background-position:center 30%;"></div>
  <div style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;right:0;bottom:0;background:linear-gradient(to top,rgba(15,23,42,0.9) 0%,rgba(15,23,42,0.45) 60%,rgba(15,23,42,0.15) 100%);"></div>
  <div style="position:relative;z-index:1;max-width:1280px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 24px 48px;width:100%;box-sizing:border-box;">
    <p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:12px;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.55);margin:0 0 12px;"><a href="/" style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.55);text-decoration:none;">Home</a> / <a href="/areas" style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.55);text-decoration:none;">Areas</a> / Pinner</p>
    <h1 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:clamp(32px,5vw,54px);font-weight:700;color:#ffffff;margin:0 0 10px;letter-spacing:-0.04em;line-height:1.05;">Plasterer in Pinner</h1>
    <p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:16px;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.75);margin:0;">HA5 · Plastering, decorating &amp; wallpapering across Pinner village and surrounds.</p>
  </div>
</section>
<section style="padding:56px 24px;background:#ffffff;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E8F0;">
  <div style="max-width:1280px;margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:12px;font-weight:600;color:#11ADE2;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;margin:0 0 12px;">About Pinner</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:clamp(20px,3vw,30px);font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;margin:0 0 18px;letter-spacing:-0.03em;line-height:1.2;">A village centre with genuine period character — Victorian and Edwardian properties around the High Street generate consistent plastering and decorating work.</h2>
    <p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:15px;color:#334155;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 14px;">Pinner village centre retains a historic character that's relatively rare for West London — genuine Victorian and Edwardian commercial and residential buildings around the High Street. The surrounding residential areas expand into 1930s suburban development. Wallpapering, skimming, and interior painting are the dominant domestic jobs. Period property owners in the village often need lime-compatible materials for older walls.</p>
    <p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:15px;color:#334155;line-height:1.75;margin:0;">Pinner is also a target area for sash window painting — the period stock has a higher density of original sash windows than most of the surrounding suburbs.</p>
  </div>
</section>
<section style="padding:56px 24px;background:#F8FAFC;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E8F0;">
  <div style="max-width:1280px;margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:12px;font-weight:600;color:#11ADE2;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;margin:0 0 12px;">Common problems</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:clamp(20px,3vw,28px);font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;margin:0 0 28px;letter-spacing:-0.03em;">What goes wrong in Pinner's housing stock.</h2>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(240px,1fr));gap:20px;">
      <div style="background:#ffffff;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:8px;padding:24px;"><h3 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;margin:0 0 8px;">Lime plaster on period walls</h3><p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:14px;color:#334155;line-height:1.65;margin:0;">The Victorian and Edwardian stock around the village has solid-brick walls and lime plaster. Patching it with modern gypsum traps moisture — these walls need breathable, compatible materials.</p></div>
      <div style="background:#ffffff;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:8px;padding:24px;"><h3 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;margin:0 0 8px;">Sash window decay</h3><p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:14px;color:#334155;line-height:1.65;margin:0;">Pinner has a higher density of original sash windows than the surrounding suburbs. When the paint film fails they let water in and the timber starts to rot — proper prep and repainting protects them.</p></div>
      <div style="background:#ffffff;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:8px;padding:24px;"><h3 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;margin:0 0 8px;">Settlement cracks on the semis</h3><p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:14px;color:#334155;line-height:1.65;margin:0;">The 1930s suburban streets around the village sit on clay — the same stepped and hairline cracking above openings that runs across Middlesex, needing repair and re-skim.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
<section style="padding:56px 24px;background:#ffffff;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E8F0;">
  <div style="max-width:1280px;margin:0 auto;">
    <div style="display:flex;gap:64px;flex-wrap:wrap;margin-bottom:48px;">
      <div style="flex:1;min-width:300px;">
        <p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:12px;font-weight:600;color:#11ADE2;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;margin:0 0 12px;">Neighbourhoods we work in</p>
        <h2 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:clamp(20px,3vw,28px);font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;margin:0 0 18px;letter-spacing:-0.03em;line-height:1.2;">A genuine village centre, ringed by Metro-land.</h2>
        <p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:15px;color:#334155;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 14px;">Pinner's High Street is a rare survival for West London — genuine Victorian and Edwardian buildings around the parish church and the old village core, much of it within a conservation area. Out from the centre, the streets expand into classic 1930s suburban Metro-land semis. The two halves need very different handling: period repair and lime work in the village, conventional skimming and crack repair on the suburban semis.</p>
        <p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:15px;color:#334155;line-height:1.75;margin:0;">It's an attractive, sought-after area where homeowners value the period character and want it maintained properly.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="flex:1;min-width:300px;">
        <p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:12px;font-weight:600;color:#11ADE2;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;margin:0 0 12px;">What homeowners ask for</p>
        <h2 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:clamp(20px,3vw,28px);font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;margin:0 0 18px;letter-spacing:-0.03em;line-height:1.2;">Wallpapering, sash windows, and skimming.</h2>
        <p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:15px;color:#334155;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 14px;">Pinner brings a strong run of wallpapering and quality interior decorating, sash window repair and repainting on the period properties, and skimming and crack repair on the suburban stock. Lime-compatible plastering is relevant on the older village walls. Exterior masonry work is scheduled for the drier months.</p>
        <p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:15px;color:#334155;line-height:1.75;margin:0;">Considered budgets, real attention to finish — and a fixed price agreed before we start.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:12px;font-weight:600;color:#11ADE2;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;margin:0 0 24px;">Working in Pinner</p>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(220px,1fr));gap:20px;">
      <div><h3 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:15px;font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;margin:0 0 8px;">~20 minutes from base</h3><p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:14px;color:#334155;line-height:1.65;margin:0;">A straightforward run from Harefield via Ruislip. A regular working area with no travel premium on the quote.</p></div>
      <div><h3 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:15px;font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;margin:0 0 8px;">Period-aware</h3><p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:14px;color:#334155;line-height:1.65;margin:0;">Conservation-area and period properties get breathable, period-appropriate materials. We assess the wall before specifying anything.</p></div>
      <div><h3 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:15px;font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;margin:0 0 8px;">Access &amp; parking</h3><p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:14px;color:#334155;line-height:1.65;margin:0;">Suburban streets are simple; the village core has narrow access and permit zones we plan loading around.</p></div>
      <div><h3 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:15px;font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;margin:0 0 8px;">Clean, tidy, insured</h3><p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:14px;color:#334155;line-height:1.65;margin:0;">Original features protected, site left tidy daily. Fully insured, City &amp; Guilds qualified, no subcontractors.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
